org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.ca.asm

Interface AsmVisitor


  • public interface AsmVisitor
    AsmVisitor is a visitor implementation to traverse a Celera Assembler .ASM file.

    The ASM file is the output of the Celera Assembler pipeline. It provides a precise description of the assembly as a hierarchical data structure. The messages are visited in a "definition before reference" order. Every identifier is defined in a visit message before it is referenced. For example, both reads will be visited before the visit method that defines these reads as a mate pair.

    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • visitLibraryStatistics

        void visitLibraryStatistics(String externalId,
                            long internalId,
                            float meanOfDistances,
                            float stdDev,
                            long min,
                            long max,
                            List<Long> histogram)
        Describes statistics about one library as observed after partial assembly.
        Parameters:
        externalId - the externally unique UID; the value is the same as the string as the DST accession field in the input frg file.
        internalId - an internal integer value that associates this message with future messages visited further on in the assembly pipeline.
        meanOfDistances - the mean of the distances between mates in this library.
        stdDev - the standard deviation for the mean distance of mate pairs in this library.
        min - the minimum distance between mate pairs in this library.
        max - the maximum distance between mate pairs in this library.
        histogram - a histogram of the distances observed in one library. A normal distribution indicates a well-constructed library; other distributions can indicate library problems.

      • visitRead

        void visitRead(String externalId,
               long internalId,
               AsmVisitor.MateStatus mateStatus,
               boolean isSingleton,
               Range clearRange)
        Visit one read and get its status in the assembly.
        Parameters:
        externalId - the unique external id of this read from the frg file.
        internalId - an internal integer value that associates this read with future messages visited further on in the assembly pipeline.
        mateStatus - the AsmVisitor.MateStatus of this read's mate.
        isSingleton - is this read a singleton. If true then this read could not be assembled; false otherwise.
        clearRange - the final clear range of this read determined by the Celera Assembler trimming modules (ex: Overlap Based Trimming).

        This is duplicated information provided for convenience.
        Parameters:
        externalIdOfRead1 - the unique id for one read.
        externalIdOfRead2 - the unique id for the other read.
        mateStatus - the combined status of the individual reads.

      • visitUnitig

        AsmUnitigVisitor visitUnitig(AsmVisitor.AsmVisitorCallback callback,
                             String externalId,
                             long internalId,
                             float aStat,
                             float measureOfPolymorphism,
                             AsmVisitor.UnitigStatus status,
                             NucleotideSequence consensusSequence,
                             QualitySequence consensusQualities,
                             long numberOfReads)
        Visit a Unitig generated by the unitigger module. Most unitigs are components of a contigs; some unitigs are themselves a contig. Some unitigs will be generated by splitting in the scaffold module; those unitigs will appear in a later message generated by the scaffold.
        Parameters:
        callback - the AsmVisitor.AsmVisitorCallback instance which can be used to callback to the parser.
        externalId - the unique external id of this unitig.
        internalId - an internal integer value that associates this unitig with future messages visited further on in the assembly pipeline.
        aStat - gives the likelihood this unitig derives from a unique locus of the genome, as opposed to being a collapse of reads from two copies of a genomic repeat. An aStat of 0 indicates no preference. Too-short unitigs have their A-stat set to zero. Negative values indicate repetitiveness. Positive values indicate uniqueness.
        measureOfPolymorphism - experimental measure of polymorphism observed between reads in the unitig. Introduced in CA version 6, not yet used by assembler.
        status - the unitig status.
        consensusSequence - the consensus of this unitig.
        consensusQualities - the consensus qualities of this unitig.
        numberOfReads - number of reads in the unitig, should always be ≥ 1.
        Returns:
        an instance of AsmUnitigVisitor to be used to visit this unitig; if a null value is returned, then this unitig is skipped by the parser.

      • visitUnitigLink

        void visitUnitigLink(String externalUnitigId1,
                     String externalUnitigId2,
                     AsmVisitor.LinkOrientation orientation,
                     AsmVisitor.OverlapType overlapType,
                     AsmVisitor.OverlapStatus status,
                     boolean isPossibleChimera,
                     int numberOfEdges,
                     float meanDistance,
                     float stddev,
                     Set<AsmVisitor.MatePairEvidence> matePairEvidence)
        Indicates connections between unitigs. They summarize the edges in the unitig graph whose nodes are unitigs. The graph's edges are induced by mate pairs that have one read in each unitig.
        Parameters:
        externalUnitigId1 - the external id of one of the unitigs.
        externalUnitigId2 - the external id of one the other unitig.
        orientation - The AsmVisitor.LinkOrientation of these two unitigs relative to each other.
        overlapType - the AsmVisitor.OverlapType.
        status - the AsmVisitor.OverlapStatus.
        isPossibleChimera - true if this unitg link a possible chimera; false otherwise.
        numberOfEdges - the number of contributing edges.
        meanDistance - the mean edge distance, may be negative.
        stddev - the standard deviation of edge distances.
        matePairEvidence - a set of AsmVisitor.MatePairEvidences that show the mate pairs that were used to determine that these two unitigs are linked.

      • visitContig

        AsmContigVisitor visitContig(AsmVisitor.AsmVisitorCallback callback,
                             String externalId,
                             long internalId,
                             boolean isDegenerate,
                             NucleotideSequence consensusSequence,
                             QualitySequence consensusQualities,
                             long numberOfReads,
                             long numberOfUnitigs,
                             long numberOfVariants)
        Describes one contig. A contig represents a contiguous span of the target genome. The contig contains a layout of reads, a layout of unitigs and any variants found in the underlying reads.
        Parameters:
        callback - the AsmVisitor.AsmVisitorCallback instance which can be used to callback to the parser.
        externalId - the unique external id of this contig.
        internalId - an internal integer value that associates this contig with future messages visited further on in the assembly pipeline.
        isDegenerate - is this contig a degenerate contig (not placed in a scaffold).
        consensusSequence - the gapped consensus sequences of this contig.
        consensusQualities - the consensus qualities of this contig.
        numberOfReads - the number of reads in this contig.
        numberOfUnitigs - the number of unitigs that have been laid out in this contig.
        numberOfVariants - the number of variant (alternate allele) consensus regions.
        Returns:
        an instance of AsmContigVisitor to be used to visit this contig; if a null value is returned, then this contig is skipped by the parser.

      • visitScaffold

        AsmScaffoldVisitor visitScaffold(AsmVisitor.AsmVisitorCallback callback,
                                 String externalId,
                                 long internalId,
                                 int numberOfContigPairs)
        Visit a scaffold that is made up of multiple contigs. A scaffold is the maximal unit of contiguous sequence output by Celera Assembler. A scaffold may consist of one contig or multiple contigs and their relative coordinates.
        Parameters:
        callback - the AsmVisitor.AsmVisitorCallback instance which can be used to callback to the parser.
        externalId - the unique external id of this scaffold.
        internalId - an internal integer value that associates this scaffold with future messages visited further on in the assembly pipeline.
        numberOfContigPairs - the number of contig pairs in this scaffold. when numberOfContigPairs = 0, then this scaffold consists of exactly one contig. When numberOfContigPairs > 0, then the scaffold consists of multiple contigs whose order, orientation and separation are derived from mate pairs.
        Returns:
        an instance of AsmScaffoldVisitor that will be used to visit the underlying scaffold data. If a null is returned, then this scaffold will be skipped.

      • visitScaffold

        void visitScaffold(AsmVisitor.AsmVisitorCallback callback,
                   String externalId,
                   long internalId,
                   String externalContigId)
        Visit a scaffold that is only made up of one contig. A scaffold is the maximal unit of contiguous sequence output by Celera Assembler. A scaffold may consist of one contig or multiple contigs and their relative coordinates. This method returns void since there is no underlying data for this scaffold since it only contains a single contig that has already been fully described.
        Parameters:
        callback - the AsmVisitor.AsmVisitorCallback instance which can be used to callback to the parser.
        externalId - the unique external id of this scaffold.
        internalId - an internal integer value that associates this scaffold with future messages visited further on in the assembly pipeline.
        externalContigId - the contig external id that is the only contig in this scaffold.

      • visitScaffoldLink

        void visitScaffoldLink(String externalScaffoldId1,
                       String externalScaffoldId2,
                       AsmVisitor.LinkOrientation orientation,
                       AsmVisitor.OverlapType overlapType,
                       AsmVisitor.OverlapStatus status,
                       int numberOfEdges,
                       float meanDistance,
                       float stddev,
                       Set<AsmVisitor.MatePairEvidence> matePairEvidence)
        Indicates connections between scaffolds. They summarize the edges in a graph whose nodes are scaffolds. The graph's edges are induced by mate pairs that have one read in each scaffold. By definition, the mates in the scaffold link were not used to build a scaffold; they may have been too few in number or inconsistent with other mates.
        Parameters:
        externalScaffoldId1 - the external id of one of the scaffolds.
        externalScaffoldId2 - the external id of one the other scaffold.
        orientation - The AsmVisitor.LinkOrientation of these two scaffold relative to each other.
        overlapType - the AsmVisitor.OverlapType.
        status - the AsmVisitor.OverlapStatus.
        numberOfEdges - the number of contributing edges.
        meanDistance - the mean edge distance, may be negative.
        stddev - the standard deviation of edge distances.
        matePairEvidence - a set of AsmVisitor.MatePairEvidences that show the mate pairs that were used to determine that these two scaffolds are linked.

      • visitEnd

        void visitEnd()
        The end of the ASM file has been reached.

      • halted

        void halted()
        The parser has stopped parsing the ASM file due to AsmVisitor.AsmVisitorCallback.haltParsing() being called. the end of the ASM file was not yet reached.
